	<phrase id="31" desc="">
		<original>
			“Baptism is an outward sign of an inward grace:” Romans 6:2-4 states that baptism is an actual participation in the death, burial and resurrection of Christ. It is not merely a sign or symbol.
		</original>
		<translated>
			
		</translated>
