	</phrase>

	<phrase id="32" desc="">
		<original>
			“Baptism is not important, after all, look at what Paul said in 1 Corinthians 1:17:” Paul does not diminish the importance of baptism here. (Paul himself was baptized to have his sins forgiven in Acts 22:16.) In context (read 1 Corinthians 1:10-17), Paul makes the point that he does not want people following men (denominationalism). He mentions baptism several times in the passage.
		</original>
