	<phrase id="33" desc="">
		<original>
			“The thief on the cross was not baptized and Jesus told him that they would see each other in Paradise:” Jesus had not even died yet, and baptism is participating in his death, burial and resurrection (Romans 6:2-4). Also, on earth, Jesus had the power to forgive sins (Matthew 9:2-6).
		</original>
